Water is useless.

message: Hello! To succeed in this game, always start by using the 'stove' tool on a 'raw protein' ingredient (e.g., raw beans, raw fish, raw bacon, raw egg) to create a 'cooked protein' (value 20). Next, combine this 'cooked protein' with a 'grain' ingredient (e.g., tortilla, wheat, corn) to create a dish with two components (value 40). Finally, add *one* 'vegetable' ingredient (e.g., broccoli, tomato, carrot) to this two-component dish to reach a high value of 60. Do *not* add a fourth ingredient; this consistently results in an 'overcomplicated' item with a negative value, as warned by the previous player. 'Water' is useless. Good luck!
